<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900413-0050</DOCNO><DOCID>900413-0050.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- McDonnell Douglas Corp.:   Israel Orders 18 Helicopters   For Total of $150 Million</HL><DATE>04/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   MD MDEST</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><LP>   McDonnell Douglas Corp. said Israel ordered 18 AH-64Ahelicopters for $150 million. But the St. Louis-basedaerospace and defense company also said that Egypt isconsidering buying 24 of the Apache attack helicopters andthat the Israeli purchase shouldn't tilt the Mideast balanceof power.   McDonnell Douglas said that Israel is the firstinternational customer for the AH-64A, and that the orderwill be completed as a foreign military sale with the U.S.government. It said the sale will provide the Israeli airforce with &quot;a stand-off weapon system with an anti-armor, dayand night missile capability.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   The first of the aircraft is scheduled to be delivered tothe Israelis during the 1990 third quarter. Several othernations in the Middle East, Europe and the Far East haveexpressed interest in buying Apaches for their own defense,McDonnell Douglas said. A spokesman said that prior to theIsraeli purchase, the U.S. Army has ordered 807 of thehelicopters since their production began in 1983.</TEXT></DOC>